Kubo Yuri was a girl born to a Hungarian-Japanese father and a Japanese mother.[l][r]
She was born in Japan, lived in both Hungary and Japan, and grew up in a relatively wealthy family.[l][r]
For some reason, she always liked guns since she was little. They say she used to run around causing a ruckus with a homemade rubber band gun.[l][r]
Eventually, it switched to toy guns, then airsoft guns, and by the time she was in high school, she was using a competitive rifle.[l][r]
Her talent stood out among her peers. She could hit any difficult target. She was a prodigy, and she knew it. She genuinely loved guns and competition.[l][r]
[r]But.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
One morning, she suddenly couldn't handle guns anymore.[l][r]
The details are still unclear. According to her parents and friends, even though the competition guns were safe and only emitted harmless beams of light, Yuri couldn't hold or aim them anymore.[l][r]
[r]From the moment she woke up that morning, she seemed different. Her mother described it as if "she had become a different person."[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[bg  time="1500"  method="crossfade"  storage="sinen.png"  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
Regardless, she couldn't participate in the competition she was looking forward to.[l][r]
She had to take a break from club activities, went to the hospital, and researched her symptoms herself, but the cause remained unknown.[l][r]
[r]Then one day, a few days later,[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[bg  time="1000"  method="crossfade"  storage="locker.jpg"  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
She was found collapsed on the clubroom floor.[l][r]
Her beautiful blue eyes were wide open and filled with tears.[l][r]
She was barely breathing.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

