My wife and I left the room and met up with Ishii-san, who was talking to Yuri's parents, and decided to discuss our thoughts in the courtyard.[l][r]

[r]"If there's some god-like entity that caused this, I'd want to hurl abuse at them forever."[l][r]
"I agree."[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
With a face mixed with anger and sorrow, Ishii-san agreed.[r]
My wife, too, was tearful from such a cruel reunion.[l][r]
[r]Yeah. Such a cruel reunion shouldn't happen. When I heard the details about Yuri, I couldn't stop trembling.[l][r]
And I thought over and over whether I should tell Chito or if it was better not to.[l][r]
[r]But knowing that sharp-witted girl, she had probably figured it out already.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"How did you explain it to Yuri's parents?"[l][r]
"We told them: we owed Yuri in the past, without going into specifics. We didn't say, 'We knew her in a past life.'[l][r]
But her parents didn't dig too deep. To them, it felt like a long-awaited answer had finally arrived."[l][r]
[r]Saying this, Ishii-san handed us a notebook. What is this...?[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"This is Yuri's diary. It's quite jumbled with treatment notes and other things besides daily entries."[l][r]
Ishii-san opened the notebook and pointed to a name.[r]
It said Kanazawa and Ishii.[l][r]
"There are other pages with our names on them as well. She must've remembered us from the other world and wrote about us.[l][r]
When I introduced myself, her parents, after exchanging surprised glances, lent me this notebook."[l][r]
...I see. That's why her parents are somewhat convinced of our connection to Yuri.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"They asked us to give this notebook to 'Chi-chan.' They pleaded, hoping it might help her wake up."[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

